@@TJvFormPlacement.Active
Summary
  Indicates whether the component automatically restores and saves the form's placement.
Description
  If Active is set to true, the component automatically restores the form's placement when the form
  is shown, and saves the form's placement when the form is closed.

  Alternatively, you can call the RestoreFormPlacement and SaveFormPlacement methods to explicitly
  restore and save the form's placement.
See Also
  RestoreFormPlacement, SaveFormPlacement

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormPlacement.AppStorage
Summary
  Links the component to a storage component.
Description
  Set AppStorage to an application storage component that gives access to a specific storage, such as
  a xml file or the registry. AppStorage allows the TJvFormPlacement component to read from and write
  to the storage.

  To allow the placement data of a form to be read or written from a storage, both the AppStorage and
  the AppStoragePath properties must be set.
See Also
  TJvFormPlacement.AppStoragePath

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormPlacement.AppStoragePath
Summary
  Specifies the location of the stored data in the storage.
Description
  Use AppStoragePath to specify the location of the stored data in the storage.

  The storage system uses paths and uses the concept of folders and values (much like folders and
  files on an OS). AppStoragePath is a path relative to the root folder of the storage component.

  To allow the placement data of a form to be read or written from a storage, both the AppStorage and
  the AppStoragePath properties must be set.
See Also
  TJvFormPlacement.AppStorage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormPlacement.EraseSections
Summary
  Erases all sections used by this component of the storage.
Description
  Call EraseSection to remove all sections, all their keys, and their data values from the storage.
See Also
  <LINK Version>

