@@TJvFormPlacement.Version
Summary
  Specifies a version number.
Description
  Use Version to prevent the component from retrieving the form's placement from out-of-date
  information in the storage.

  The Version number is stored together with the form's placement information in the storage. Then,
  before
  the component retrieves the placement info from the storage, it compares the stored version number
  with
  the value specified by Version. If the stored version is less then the value specified by Version,
  the component does <i>not</i> retrieve the placement info.

  Thus increase Version each time stored placement information becomes out-of-date.
See Also
  TJvFormPlacement.EraseSections

