@@TJvFormStorage
<TITLEIMG TJvFormStorage>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.FormsAndApp.Sizing,
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  General storage component.
Description
  Use a TJvFormStorage component to store and retrieve data from a storage - either the system
  registry or an ini file. The component can store, retrieve and restore published properties of any
  component on the form.

  For example you can use the component to save the position of a splitter, the text of an edit control or the checked value of a ch
  ckbox on closure of a form, and later retrieve and restore the properties of these components on
  re-opening of the form.

  TJvFormStorage descends from TJvFormPlacement; thus, it also enables you to store and retrieve the
  forms placement.

  To use this component, do the following:

  * Drop a TJvFormStorage on a form.
  * Use either the <LINK TJvFormStorage_StoredProps_Editor,StoredProps editor> by double-clicking
    the component, or the component's properties, to specify which properties of what components
    you want to be stored and retrieved.
  * Use the AppStorage property to link the component to a storage component.
  * Use AppStoragePath to specify the location in the storage to save and read the data to.
  * You can then set property <LINK TJvFormPlacement.Active,Active> to true to allow automatically
    save and restore the specified properties, or call the <LINK TJvFormPlacement.RestoreFormPlacement,
    RestoreFormPlacement> and <LINK TJvFormPlacement.SaveFormPlacement,SaveFormPlacement> methods
    at run-time to retrieve and store the form.
  * Link the TJvFormStorage (or TJvFormPlacement) component to the IniStorage property of other
    components to save and load information specific for these components (TJvCheckListBox,
    TJvDrawGrid, TJvSpeedbar, TJvMRUManager, TJvDBGrid) with no additional code.
See Also
  TJvFormPlacement

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage.DefaultValue
Summary
  References the stored values in the list by their name.
Description
  Use the DefaultValue property to get or set the value represented by a stored value object with a
  particular name.

  If you use DefaultValue to <i>get</i> the value of a stored value object that is NULL, DefaultValue
  returns the value represented by the Default parameter. If you try to <i>set</i> the value of a
  stored value object to NULL, then it is actually set to the value represented by the Default
  parameter.
Parameters
  Name     - Identifies the name of the stored value.
  DefValue - Specifies a value to use if the stored value is not in the storage.
See Also
  TJvFormStorage.StoredValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage.SetNotification
Summary
  Ensures that the storage component is notified that a component with a stored property is going to
  be destroyed.
Description
  SetNotification is called by the storage component, after an update of StoredProps. It ensures that
  the components whose properties are listed in StoredProps notify the storage component when they
  are going to be destroyed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage.StoredProps
Summary
  Lists all controls and their stored properties, that are managed by the storage component.
Description
  Use StoredProps to directly determine the components and their properties that are managed by the
  storage component. The format of the list is:

 
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  component.property 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>

  Thus for example:

 
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  CheckBox1.Checked
  Button1.Caption 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>

  A <LINK TJvFormStorage_StoredProps_Editor,StoredProps editor> is provided for design-time editing
  of the StoredProps property.
See Also
  TJvFormStorage.StoredValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage.StoredValue
Summary
  References the stored values in the list by their name.
Description
  Use the StoredValue property to get or set the value represented by a stored value object with a
  particular name.
See Also
  TJvFormStorage.DefaultValue, TJvFormStorage.StoredProps, TJvStoredValues.Items,
  TJvStoredValues.Values

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage.StoredValues
Summary
  Contains the stored values for a storage component.
Description
  Access StoredValues at runtime to view and set stored value names and values dynamically (at design time use the collection editor f
  r the StoredProps property to set stored value information). StoredValues can be accessed as a
  zero-based array of TJvStoredValue objects.
  Index specifies the array element to access.

  The following code assumes that the storage component has 3 stored value objects, and sets and
  stores their values:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  JvFormStorage1.StoredValues[0].Value := 'Germany';
  JvFormStorage1.StoredValues[1].Value := 'Berlin';
  JvFormStorage1.StoredValues[2].Value := 10331000;
  JvFormStorage1.StoredValues.SaveValues; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
Note
  An easier way to set and retrieve values of stored value objects when the name of each stored value
  object is known is to call StoredValue; however, StoredValue cannot be used to change a stored
  value’s name.
See Also
  TJvFormStorage.StoredValue, TJvStoredValues, TJvStoredValues.Items

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormStorage_StoredProps_Editor
<TITLE StoredProps editor> <HASTOCENTRY OFF> <Description>
Use the StoredProps editor to define which properties to store and retrieve by the TJvFormStorage component.

To open the StoredProps editor:

1. Place a TJvFormStorage component on the form.
2. Do one of the following:

  * Double-click that component, or
  * With the component selected, double-click the StoredProps property in the Object Inspector
    to invoke the StoredProps editor.

<b>Form Properties</b>

\Check the "Active Control" control to let the storage component store on closing of the form and retrieve and restore on showing of the form, the control that has focus on the form.

\Check "Form Position" to indicate that the component should store and retrieve the placement of the form: the form's normal, minimized and maximized size and position and its minimum and maximum tracking size.

\Check the "Window State" control to indicate that the way how the form
appears on the screen - minimized, maximized, or in a normal state - should be stored and retrieved by the component.

<b>Stored Properties</b>

To add a property of a component to the storage component:

1. Select the component where from a property to add in the Components list.
2. Select the property of the component to add in the Properties list.
3. Choose Add.

The selected component and its property are displayed in the Stored Properties list box. For example,
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
CheckBox1.Checked 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  TJvFormStorage.StoredProps

